>  The 'vent' system is fresh air coming thru the vent on the nose between the
> turn signals. You operate by moving the blue lever down. The blue one is next
> to the 2 red ones to the right of the blank hole in the cluster.
> 
>  The fan switch you are turning sounds like you have an air conditioning
> system installed in the bus..... another giveaway that you have air
> conditioning is the 'radiator looking part'!

almost for sure, the A/C has a squirrel cage blower fan behind the dash,
this means you probably also have a second lower dash panel with vents in
it below the regular dash..the sound you hear is probably the A/C blower
that is messed up not the heater blower, the heater blower is mounted to
the top of the engine compartment, it has two ducts one runninng to each
side of the engine towards the rear.

Bob

